race.comment: ZALE (8) runs along and seeks the hat-trick off wins at Bathurst and Queanbeyan. He's improving and has early tow. CALLENEM THRU (13) was backed off the map winning a 50 at Canberra, and he was expected to win a CL2 there following and settled last beaten 3L. Peaks for this and is a live chance. STUPENDO (1) found Open grade too tough at Wagga but led and won a CL3 here prior. Has to carry top weight in easier and skip across from the 8 barrier. Collett's booking is a positive and he can't be ruled out. SACRED MISTRESS (5) resumes for the Pepper yard. Has jumped a short-priced favourite in his last six outings and goes fresh and over this distance. Has to be kept very safe.
